Text: In this first week of the studio projects we were to understand what is expected of us.
This was done through reading up on the content provided, researching the project briefs and what is to be expected of the teams who choose to work on these projects.

I appreciated the time Teacher1 and Teacher2 took to explain the plan for the studio projects in upcoming weeks, although I failed to use my imagination when it came to .selecting my preferences of which 2 studio projects I preferred out of the 7 available options.
I wanted to know about what each project had to offer more in depth before selecting.
When it came to discussing with the other SHIFT students what their project selection and preferences were, it proved to be a little more difficult.
Some students, such as .myself, were more than willing to compromise on what project team they were going to join, with the objective of getting gender diversity and more than three in a team.
I believe the more adaptable students who were willing to try any project were looking to challenge themselves and saw it as an opportunity to try something different.
Some students felt passionately about specific projects which were to be expected, although the decision became difficult at times with the unwillingness to compromise.
I found that interesting because I personally didn't attach myself to any one project and saw opportunity in them all seeing as the brief was not very descriptive.
I did however .have some people I was eager to work with in mind as team dynamics are so important in agile projects such as this one.
Once we were in our teams and everyone felt comfortable with the team they were placed in, we split up to allocate roles within the team.
Our project is looking at extracting .data and creating a dashboard for a small company called Ocean Browser, something none of us have done before.
Roro preferred this project because he wanted to grow .his experience in data extraction, as did Toto.

I myself donâ€™t personally know whether this project suits my skills although I look forward to learning something new and applying .my learnings from the paper I have been taking this semester focused on developing information systems.

This made allocating roles easy; Toto decided to be involved with data .visualisation and extraction; Roro, server coding and data extraction; Myself, analysing and designing the database as well as UX.
Our next step is speaking with our client and extracting information from them with the interview script we have been working on.
This part I am looking forward to.

I have been .involved with business and entrepreneurship which has involved a lot of speaking to potential customers, understanding their problems and trying to solve it in a meaningful and .human centered way.
